b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48289.htm)  [Next](sbe48291.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n44\\. Moreover it is so stated in Sm _ri_ ti.\n\nSm _ri_ ti moreover declares the individual soul to be a part of the highest\nPerson, 'An eternal part of myself becomes\n\np. 563\n\nthe individual soul ( _g_ iva) in the world of life' (Bha. Gi. XV, 7). For\nthis reason also the soul must be held to be a part of Brahman.\n\nBut if the soul is a part of Brahman, all the imperfections of the soul are\nBrahman's also! To this objection the next Sutra replies.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 45. But as in the case of light...](sbe48291.htm)\n\n"